WEBVTT

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:01.845
they agree on what quality is,

00:06:01.845 --> 00:06:05.559
they start measuring, they share the data,

00:06:05.559 --> 00:06:09.075
they find who's best, and they learn from it.

00:06:09.075 --> 00:06:11.667
Continuous improvement.

00:06:11.667 --> 00:06:14.215
Now, that's not the only exciting part.

00:06:14.215 --> 00:06:16.466
That's exciting in itself.

00:06:16.466 --> 00:06:19.417
But if you bring back the cost side of the equation,

00:06:19.417 --> 00:06:20.877
and look at that,

00:06:20.877 --> 00:06:23.882
it turns out, those who have focused on quality,

00:06:23.882 --> 00:06:25.915
they actually also have the lowest costs,

00:06:25.915 --> 00:06:28.584
although that's not been the purpose
in the first place.

00:06:28.584 --> 00:06:31.614
So if you look at the hip surgery story again,